        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 31:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " it is used in the description of ‘the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "virtuous",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " woman’; also in this chapter, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Kings 1:52",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", we have the word translated ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "worthy;",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 9:13",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " it is used of those who were ‘very ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "able",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " men’ for the work of the service of the house of the Lord. In the present case it was not so much a man of valour as of discretion who was needed in the messenger.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and bringest good tidings",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The expression is somewhat redundant in the Hebrew, and might be rendered ‘bringest good tidings of good’. The same words are thus translated ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
